For fresh instals of this app on a new pc, install firebase-tools.



To deploy for similar App build-outs...

Launch firebase UI by running "firebase login" from the command line.

From the command line run "firebase init".   Initializes a Firebase project in the terminal's directory \.

This app's firebase init selection includes the following:
-(*) Hosting: Configure files for Firebase Hosting and (optionally) set up GitHub Action deploys.
-Public directory is set to build, no parentheses.
-y for single page application (Because this is a React app)
-Set up auto builds and deploys with Github - y
-Set up the workflow to run a build script before every deploy? - y
-What script should be run before every deploy? - npm ci && npm run build
-Set up automatic deployment to your site's live channel when a PR is merged? - Y
-What is the name of the GitHub branch associated with your site's live channel? - master

Create production build after initialization is complete:
npm run build

to deploy - firebase deploy

Project Console: https://console.firebase.google.com/project/clone-14498/overview
Hosting URL: https://clone-14498.web.app

*After code updates, run npm build again to move changes into the build.




